China Establishes Files for Giant Pandas
CHENGDU , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- Chinese experts have established files for 37 giant pandas living in the Tangjiahe Nature Reserve in southwest China 's Sichuan Province to monitor their genetic identity and strengthen the protection of these rare animals .
The files include the total number , sex , and blood relationships of the giant pandas in the reserve .
The Tangjiahe Reserve is located in northern Sichuan 's Longmen Mountain area which neighbors Gansu Province .
It is estimated that there are some 1,000 giant pandas in the world , and 80 percent of them live in Sichuan Province .
